Welche Aussage passt zum mobilen Verhalten?<br><div class="code-card" style="max-width:900px;border-radius:16px;overflow:hidden;background:#102d42;box-shadow:0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.16);font-family:Consolas,'Courier New',monospace;margin:12px 0;"><div style="height:42px;background:#12334a;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14);display:flex;align-items:center;padding:0 16px;color:#fff;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-weight:700;"><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#ff5f57;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:7px;"></span><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#ffbd2e;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:7px;"></span><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#28c840;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:13px;"></span>style.css</div><pre style="margin:0;padding:18px 20px;color:#f8fbff;line-height:1.48;font-size:15px;white-space:pre-wrap;background:#102d42;">@media (max-width: 700px) {
  .nav-list {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}</pre></div>

